<div id="centerhub-description" class="desc">
  <h3>Center Hub:</h3>
  <p>
    The central unit responsible for collecting and processing data from various
    sensors placed throughout the home. It acts as the main communication hub,
    ensuring all sensor data is accurately received and transmitted to other
    system components for further analysis and action.
  </p>
</div>

<div id="fire-description" class="desc">
  <h3>Fire Sensor:</h3>
  <p>
    A sensor that detects the presence of fire or smoke using infrared,
    ultraviolet, or heat-based detection methods. It is used in fire alarm
    systems for safety.
  </p>
</div>

<div id="gas-description" class="desc">
  <h3>Gas Sensor:</h3>
  <p>
    A sensor that detects specific gases in the air, such as carbon monoxide,
    methane, or air pollutants. It is used in environmental monitoring and
    industrial safety.
  </p>
</div>

